Steinway street has some tough competition when it comes to authentic North African food, but hands down, this is the best Moroccan restaurant in the area and possibly all of Queens. Anything coming off the grill is delightful. Falafels are great as well. Highly recommended when you are in the area. Indoor seating is limited so not suited for a formal dinner, but with enough outdoor seating, great for a casual alfresco dining. Gets crowded at nighttime during Ramadan since it’s across a mosque and they have an Iftar (breaking of the fast) menu. In the winter, you might be better off doing a takeout.

This place has been in business for a long time in Astoria, and it shows. Although the insides are dated, the food is high quality and delicious. I especially enjoy eating their numerous North African offerings in their outdoor seating area when the weather is nice. Platters and sandwiches are all very good.

Is A little restaurant on Steinway Street, Astoria, selling ethnic moroccon food. Couscous, a North African grainy pasta served with a soupy vegetable broth with chicken or lamb, available on Fridays ONLY. TAGINE (Baked) lamb or chicken with peas,,, MERGUEZ (Lamb and beef with Moroccan spices) is a typical halal sausage you can only find in ALGERIA, TUNISIA AND MOROCCO served with French fries or as a Sandwich and many more.....

Parking is tough in this neighborhood so taking public transportation is best or be prepared to park a few blocks away.

ATMOSPHERE: - Small place on a corner with outside seating. - Being that it's on a street you are going to get whatever noise comes with the traffic outside.  SERVICE: - The staff, at least during lunch, wasn't that accommodating. FOOD: - Lamb Kebab - Yellow Rice - Salad (Lettuce, corn, beets, vinegar, and oil...olive oil???) - Prices: $13. - The portions were small and not very satisfying.
